Subject: Re: [T2] towing question

On Tue, 23 Apr 2002, Sean Bartnik wrote:

> The manual transmission will be lubricated as the gears inside turn through
> the gear oil.  You can't do this with an automatic because the automatic has
> a hydraulic pump that isn't running if the engine is off, and therefore the
> transmission wouldn't be properly lubricated rolling along in neutral with
> the engine off.

right the manual transmission has a "splash" lubrication system.  the
gears run through the oil and "splash" enough of it around to lub the
tranny
while
the auto tranny has a presure lube system much like an engine, the lube
pump, pumps tranny fluid through the gears and other critical parts. 

Bob


